reviews.title: What a nice Resto Bar!
reviews.text: Today we had a lovely lunch at Urk. Umai Resto Bar offers original, tasteful dishes at a reasonable price. We have chosen the 3 course Chef’s Choice. Started with some delicious oysters, really delicious homemade marinated olives and naan bread with a dip. Then starter of carpaccio with delicious tuna, head was a tender duck with smoked mashed potatoes and mushroom and after a salted caramel ice cream with fresh Dutch strawberries and cookies. Super friendly and professional service and a nice atmosphere. We were inside but there is also a fantastic terrace with nice seating. Highly recommended, we love to come back. Thanks and see you next time!

reviews.title: A special restaurant with excellent service.
reviews.text: Our group of friends consists of 8 people and we regularly visit restaurants in both the Netherlands and abroad. We chose the five-course surprise menu. Every course was indeed a delicious surprise. We just really enjoyed it. What stood out was the excellent service. You don't get to see that a lot these days. Friendly, correct and witty in time. All in all it was a very successful dinner.

articleContent.title: Your go-to guide for dog-friendly travel

seoInfo.metaDescription: Traveling with your dog has never been easier—or more fun. Cities across the country boast pet-friendly hotels, parks, and activities. With CESAR® brand’s mission to make the world more pet-friendly and Tripadvisor’s top-rated spots, you can plan with confidence. Whether it’s a quick getaway or a bucket-list trip, our guides help you stay, play, and explore with your pup. Grab the leash and go!

articleContent.title: Meet the Ascend Collection resorts travelers are buzzing about

seoInfo.metaDescription: If a resort getaway is on your list this year, look no further. Earning top ratings, Ascend Collection resorts stand out with premium amenities and memorable cultural experiences. Discover what you’ll love about these one-of-a-kind resorts and unmissable destinations in this roundup inspired by real traveler reviews.

With a week in Barcelona, you’ll feel like a local in no time. I put together this seven-day itinerary with that goal, introducing you to one neighborhood at a time, giving you a chance to get to know each spot really well before moving on to the next. (It also means there’s very little backtracking, which means saving on travel time as well. Win-win!) So if you want to get lost on the narrow streets of the Gothic Quarter, ride a bicycle along the beaches of Barceloneta, or window-shop in the Art Nouveau boutiques along the Passeig de Gràcia, this itinerary is for you.

reviews.title: Top food and friendly staff
reviews.text: Very tasty food, beautifully prepared dishes with fantastic taste. It's not cheap, but you definitely get your money's worth! We chose the Chefs Choice, where we each got 6 dishes. This way we didn't have to choose from the menu ourselves, which was nice, because everything sounded delicious! Also very friendly staff

reviews.title: Fantastic!
reviews.text: What a delicious meal we had here! Looking for a restaurant near our hotel we found Umai. An inviting menu and good reviews - we quickly turned around and booked a table. We were warmly welcomed and shown to our table. Although the a la carte dishes looked great, we decided on the chef's 6-course surprise menu. It was amazing! Exceeded expectations with beautiful, small dishes packed with flavor. It was so delicious that halfway through we decided to make it an 8-course dinner. The service was also great! Friendly and pleasant and they knew what they were talking about. This restaurant is definitely highly recommended! Unfortunately for us suburbanites, we don't live nearby, but we would love to come back!

reviews.title: Pure enjoyment
reviews.text: A culinary experience in a beautiful place. Everything is correct! The atmosphere, the dishes, the friendly service. Nothing is too much for them and they talk passionately about the dishes. The chef knows exactly what he is doing. Normally I'm a farmer and I don't eat anything I don't know, but I can honestly say that everything was more than delicious. The dishes were inviting, surprising and challenging. The wines were perfectly matched to the dishes. The restaurant is beautiful and the service is extremely friendly, with a love for their profession and expertise. And the cocktails are sublime. This is certainly not the last time we will be here. Highly recommended for everyone.

What a wonderful experience! The Chef's Choice menu with various snacks from the lunch menu over 6 courses was not only delicious, but also so generous that we couldn't even finish it. A culinary highlight at Restaurant Bleu in Urk.
 In addition, the friendly staff of Restaurant Bleu deserves a compliment. The attentive service contributed to the pleasant atmosphere, which went perfectly with the tasteful design of the restaurant. A complete and memorable dining experience.

reviews.title: Fantastic restaurant
reviews.text:
In a word, a truly fantastic restaurant. You enter this beautiful restaurant and are greeted with a super enthusiastic and friendly welcome by the employees.
Then very good, fast and friendly service was provided at your table. Beautiful wine list and a delicious choice of very nice dishes.
We had chosen to be surprised by the chef with 5 courses. Which was a perfect choice. It was a true feast, beautiful fresh products and so tasty. We can definitely recommend this restaurant and will definitely come back here again. Restaurant Blue, thank you for your hospitality, we enjoyed it!

We had the opportunity to dine here once before and that was also a culinary experience of a high standard. The atmosphere is warm and cozy...just like the people who work there. We will definitely come back here.

reviews.title: Culinary Surprise in Urk
reviews.text: During our traditional sailing trip in September, we sailed to Urk this year because of the wind direction. It had been a while since we had been here. Things have changed in a very positive way. "via via" also reserved with Blue. This was certainly the most positive highlight of our trip. Enjoyed the four-course menu, a wonderful culinary surprise with matching wine. Afterwards we had a nice drink at the bar with the owner in a casual, almost family atmosphere. Thank you for this very successful evening.

reviews.title: Accidental fantastic discovery!
reviews.text:
If you visit Urk, eat at Blue! There you will be decorated the way you want to be decorated! Everything is correct!
And what wonderful taste sensations, unprecedented!! We were moored opposite this restaurant on our boat and by chance we ended up here.
This will be a reason to sail to Urk more often! 👌🏼👌🏼

reviews.title: Highly recommended for gourmets
reviews.text:
Fantastic from A to Z.
Lovely atmosphere, very clean, knowledgeable and friendly staff and the food was far above expectations.
The wine arrangement is highly recommended.
The explanation of each course and why the wine was chosen made it a very educational evening.
Each course was an explosion of flavors.
We would love to come back here!

reviews.title: We had a fabulous experience here
reviews.text: Yes, it's on the expensive side, but it's definitely no tourist trap. Staff spoke English and even a bit of German and was very friendly and attentive, especially towards our children. Everything from the fancy interior even down to the background music absolutely met my taste. And the food was simply delicious, including the dessert. Everything was fresh and of high quality. Would love to have a couples' night out here some time.

reviews.title: Best restaurant in Urk
reviews.text: Great restaurant in yacht haven. Amazing kitchen, best sushi, beautiful interior and very friendly stuff! Also a very good choice of wine.

reviews.title: Food was delicious, waitress was pleasant but manager was too snobbish sadly
reviews.text:
Good food, pleasant waitress but snobbish manager. Too bad!! Won't go back anymore.
We just had lunch and enjoyed the sushi and sashimi we ordered. The girl who served us was really friendly. However, the  manager was very snobbish sadly. He went to say hello to guests of every table except our table. As we were walking out after lunch,1 he did not even bother to say a simple "Thank you"

reviews.title: Superb!
reviews.text: One of the best restaurant experiences I have had in the Netherlands. The food was superb and the staff was very friendly and helpful.

reviews.title: 2 VISITS IN 3 DAYS
reviews.text: The food was above expectations the first visit. Fusion between traditional and Asian foods. Order one dish, share and order the next. A joy and to eat. Relaxed and superb food. We loved it so much we went 2 days later again.Friendly and efficient service. Shame I have to wait until next year when I will again visit Urk during the summer on my boat.IT IS A MUST VISIT!

reviews.title: Absolute gem in Urk!
reviews.text: Excellent and very fresh fusion sushi and creative Asian plates, good quality and unique ingredients, modern minimalist decor, friendly and very attentive staff, simple but good quality wine list. And VERY reasonably priced! Don't miss out. Perfect for a post sail dinner. We will certainly be back next time we are in Urk.
